    <div class="A-blue-header clearfix colelem" id="u25840-4" data-muse-uid="U25840" data-muse-type="txt_frame"><!-- content -->
     <p>Sevis appoints Christoph Fitih as Vice President, Sales for Africa</p>
    </div>
    <!-- /m_editable -->
    <!-- m_editable region-id="editable-static-tag-U25846-BP_infinity" template="meet-our-new-vp-sales-in-africa.html" data-type="html" data-ice-options="disableImageResize,link" -->
    <div class="news-date clearfix colelem" id="u25846-4" data-muse-uid="U25846" data-muse-type="txt_frame"><!-- content -->
     <p>Date: May 3rd, 2016</p>
    </div>
    <!-- /m_editable -->
    <div class="clearfix colelem" id="pu25962"><!-- group -->
     <!-- m_editable region-id="editable-static-tag-U25962-BP_infinity" template="meet-our-new-vp-sales-in-africa.html" data-type="image" -->
     <div class="rounded-corners clip_frame grpelem" id="u25962" data-muse-uid="U25962" data-muse-type="img_frame"><!-- image -->
      <img class="block" id="u25962_img" src="/images/christoph%20fitih.jpg?crc=255675935" alt="" width="225" height="259" data-muse-src="/images/christoph%20fitih.jpg?crc=255675935" />
     </div>
     <!-- /m_editable -->
     <!-- m_editable region-id="editable-static-tag-U25843-BP_infinity" template="meet-our-new-vp-sales-in-africa.html" data-type="html" data-ice-options="disableImageResize,link" -->
     <div class="body clearfix grpelem" id="u25843-11" data-muse-uid="U25843" data-muse-type="txt_frame"><!-- content -->
      <p><span id="u25843">Dallas, Texas: </span>Sevis Systems, the leading developer of wireless backhaul optimization and acceleration technology, today announced that Christoph Fitih has joined the company as Vice President, Sales for Africa.</p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
      <p>With over 18 years of multi-national and multi-cultural experience in the technology sector, including services to mobile operators and rural communities, Mr. Fitih will be responsible for the design and implementation of the company’s business development and sales strategy across Africa.</p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
      <p>“Christoph has a track record of developing strong customer relationships and delivering innovative solutions for mobile carriers in Africa” said Tim Peyla, Sevis’ Vice President, Global Business Development. “His expertise and understanding of the challenges and opportunities facing mobile and satellite operators will be essential, as we capitalize on the use of new, next-generation high throughput satellites in time for the much-needed expansion of mobile 3G and LTE services in the region. I look forward to working closely with Christoph to deliver the improved economics and performance that allow African mobile network operators to expand voice and data coverage.”</p>
     </div>
     <!-- /m_editable -->
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix colelem" id="pu8258"><!-- group -->
     <div id="u8258"><!-- simple frame --></div>
     <div class="clip_frame" id="u8259" data-href="page:U84"><!-- image -->
      <!-- m_editable region-id="editable-static-tag-U8259-BP_infinity" template="_system/contentholders/_u8259_bp_infinity.html" data-type="image" data-ice-options="clickable" data-ice-editable="link" -->
<a class="bc_ch_wrapper nonblock nontext" href="contact.html" data-muse-uid="U8259" data-muse-type="img_frame"><img class="block" id="u8259_img" src="/images/1407190795_680691-mail.png?crc=4275134914" alt="" width="30" height="30" data-muse-src="/images/1407190795_680691-mail.png?crc=4275134914"/></a>
<!-- /m_editable -->
     </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix colelem" id="pu25841-30"><!-- group -->
     <!-- m_editable region-id="editable-static-tag-U25841-BP_infinity" template="meet-our-new-vp-sales-in-africa.html" data-type="html" data-ice-options="disableImageResize,link" -->
     <div class="body clearfix grpelem" id="u25841-30" data-muse-uid="U25841" data-muse-type="txt_frame"><!-- content -->
      <p>Prior to joining Sevis, Mr. Fitih served as VP, EMEA Region at TECPL, and was a member of the management team that created this venture through an agreement with a major satellite company to promote, market, and sell 2G/3G Small Cell Solutions. Mr. Fitih has also held senior management and consulting positions of responsibility at U.S., U.K. and Ireland-based companies such as DataMi, Chelmsford, Parallel Wireless, Nashua, Altobridge, Viotech, and CAP Gemini, where he started his career in 1997 as Senior Managing Consultant. He is also a member in the steering committee for the first Google.org ICT Centers in rural Africa managed by Camfed; a leading NGO dedicated to eradicating poverty in Africa through the empowerment of young women.</p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
      <p>Commenting on his appointment, Christoph Fitih said “I am excited to join Sevis during such transitional times for both the wireless and satellite industries. The intersection of trends taking place simultaneously at these two industries presents enormous opportunities for African mobile networks to expand voice and data services cost-effectively, empowered by Sevis’ wireless and satellite-aware optimization and acceleration technology.”</p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
      <p>Mr. Christoph Fitih studied History and Philosophy of Science and technology at the University College London. Being currently based in Ghana, Mr. Fitih will be key as Sevis continues to expand its on-the-ground business and technical presence globally. In this role he will work closely with Tim Peyla, Global VP Business Development and the Sevis teams in Dallas, Argentina, Singapore, Phoenix and Washington, D.C.</p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
      <p id="u25841-11">About Sevis Systems</p>
      <p>Sevis Systems’ best-in-class products offer innovative solutions for mobile network operators worldwide. Sevis Systems bridges the gap between transport solutions, mobile domain expertise and deep packet inspection capabilities; offering best-in- industry support with unprecedented warranties and post product deployment services. Many of the world’s largest mobile operators rely on Sevis products to enable new services and increase operational efficiencies within their networks. Sevis ́ products are sold worldwide via a network of OEM and distribution partners. Founded in 1999, Sevis is a privately held corporation based in Dallas, Texas USA. Remote offices are located in Phoenix, Washington, D.C., Argentina, Ghana and Singapore.</p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
      <p id="u25841-16">Media Contact:</p>
      <p>Tim Peyla</p>
      <p>Vice President, Business Development Sevis Systems</p>
      <p>Phone: (1) 480 570-6400</p>
      <p>Email: <a class="nonblock" href="mailto:tim.peyla@sevis.com" target="_blank">tim.peyla@sevis.com</a></p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
     </div>
